<nav class="nav" id="nav" data-screen-label="Nav"><svg class="sunmark" viewBox="0 0 32 32" aria-hidden="true"><circle class="sun-disc" cx="16" cy="16" r="10"></circle></svg><a class="wm" href="/">AMPM <small>BUILDING SERVICES</small></a><div class="links"><a href="/services/" class="">Services</a><a href="/work/" class="">Work</a><a href="/compliance/" class="">Compliance</a><a href="/about/" class="">About</a><a href="/contact/" class="">Contact</a></div><a class="phone" href="tel:03300430080">0330 043 0080</a></nav><div class="page" style="--svc: var(--m-orange);"><div class="shell"><section class="sec p-hero"><div class="reveal in"><span class="svc-bar" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span></div><div class="reveal in"><div class="kicker">Services · 03</div></div><h1 class="reveal d1 in">External Envelope incl. Roofing</h1><p class="lede reveal d2 in">The external envelope, end to end — from rainscreen and curtain walling to flat and pitched roofing. With the Building Safety Act reshaping façade work, our <strong>compliance-led approach to remediation and Higher-Risk Buildings</strong> is the sharpest reason to put fabric with us.</p><div class="reveal d3 in" style="margin-top: 28px;"><a class="btn line sm" href="/contact/">Enquire about fabric / envelope →</a></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">What we deliver</div><h2 class="dhead sm">The full Fabric scope,<br>self-delivered.</h2></div><div class="capgroups reveal in"><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span><a href="/fabric/facade-cladding/" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px;text-decoration-thickness:2px;">Façade &amp; cladding</a></span></h4><ul><li>Rainscreen &amp; cladding</li><li>Curtain walling</li><li>Brick &amp; repointing</li><li>Render &amp; EWI</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span><a href="/fabric/roofing/" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px;text-decoration-thickness:2px;">Roofing</a></span></h4><ul><li>Flat — GRP, EPDM, single-ply</li><li>Pitched roofing</li><li>Waterproofing systems</li><li>Planned maintenance</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span><a href="/fabric/bsa-remediation/" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px;text-decoration-thickness:2px;">BSA remediation</a></span></h4><ul><li>Cladding remediation</li><li>Fire-safety envelope works</li><li>Façade repair</li><li>Higher-Risk Building scope</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span><a href="/fabric/survey-compliance/" style="color:inherit;text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px;text-decoration-thickness:2px;">Survey &amp; compliance</a></span></h4><ul><li>Condition surveys</li><li>Insurance reinstatement</li><li>Envelope upgrade programmes</li><li>Golden-thread records</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">How we work</div><h2 class="dhead sm">From survey to handover —<br>and beyond.</h2></div><ol class="steps reveal in"><li class="step"><span class="step-n">01</span><div><h4>Survey &amp; fire-strategy review</h4><p>We survey the existing envelope, assess its condition and review the fire strategy — checking cladding, render, roofing and façade against Part B and the building’s risk profile before a brick is touched.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">02</span><div><h4>Design &amp; specification</h4><p>Coordinated design and specification for cladding, rainscreen, curtain walling, render or EWI — thermal performance to Part L, fire performance to BS 8414 / BR 135, and a fully traceable spec.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">03</span><div><h4>Access &amp; enabling</h4><p>Scaffold, MEWPs and mast-climbers planned and erected safely around occupied buildings, with the enabling and strip-out works that the new envelope depends on.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">04</span><div><h4>Envelope installation</h4><p>Rainscreen, render, curtain walling, roofing, EWI and façade repairs self-delivered to the approved spec — sequenced elevation-by-elevation to keep the building weather-tight throughout.</p></div></li><li class="step"><span class="step-n">05</span><div><h4>Inspection, handover &amp; warranties</h4><p>Inspection and testing against the specification, a complete records pack, then a clean handover with product and workmanship warranties — and planned maintenance if you want us to keep the envelope sound.</p></div></li></ol></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">Standards &amp; compliance</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Built to the codes that<br>matter on handover.</h2></div><div class="capgroups reveal in"><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span>The standards we build to</span></h4><ul><li>Building Regulations Part L (thermal) &amp; Part B (fire)</li><li>BS 8414 &amp; BR 135 — cladding fire performance</li><li>Building Safety Act 2022 — higher-risk buildings</li><li>PAS 2030 / 2035 — retrofit &amp; EWI</li><li>CWCT standards — curtain walling &amp; cladding</li><li>BS 5534 — slating &amp; tiling; CDM 2015 throughout</li></ul></div><div class="capgroup"><h4><span class="dot" style="background: var(--m-orange);"></span><span>Backed by AMPM Group</span></h4><ul><li>The Group’s accreditations behind every job</li><li>29 years of group trading history, since 1997</li><li>One project manager accountable per programme</li><li>Safe working at height around occupied buildings</li><li>PQQ and reference packs on request</li></ul></div></div></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">Sectors</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Where the envelope<br>matters most.</h2></div><div class="sectorrow reveal in"><span class="sector">Higher-risk residential (HRB)</span><span class="sector">Commercial</span><span class="sector">Industrial &amp; logistics</span><span class="sector">Education</span><span class="sector">Healthcare</span><span class="sector">Heritage &amp; refurbishment</span><span class="sector">Public sector</span></div><p class="body" style="margin-top:22px;max-width:60ch;">We deliver fabric and building-envelope packages across London and the South East — including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire — for direct clients, Tier-1 main contractors and blue-chip FM providers.</p></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="intro2 reveal in"><div><div class="kicker">Market drivers</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Where the work<br>is coming from.</h2></div><p class="body">Building-envelope upgrade programmes, landlord compliance, façade and cladding remediation on Higher-Risk Buildings, and insurance reinstatement works.</p></div></section><section class="sec"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 32px;"><div class="kicker">Representative projects</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Fabric work, in the field.</h2></div><div class="caselist reveal in"><div class="case-card"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1599707367072-cd6ada2bc375?auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=900&amp;q=75" alt="CASE — Fabric" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block; object-fit:cover;" /><span class="ctag" style="background: var(--m-orange); position: absolute;">Fabric · Remediation</span><h4>HRB residential — London</h4><p class="cs">Cladding remediation and fire-safety envelope works on a Higher-Risk Building.</p><div class="cm"><div><div class="k">Value</div><div class="v">£3.2m</div></div><div><div class="k">Programme</div><div class="v">34 wks</div></div></div></div><div class="case-card"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1632759145351-1d592919f522?auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=900&amp;q=75" alt="CASE — Fabric" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block; object-fit:cover;" /><span class="ctag" style="background: var(--m-orange); position: absolute;">Fabric · Roofing</span><h4>Industrial estate — South East</h4><p class="cs">Single-ply flat-roof replacement across multiple units.</p><div class="cm"><div><div class="k">Value</div><div class="v">£820k</div></div><div><div class="k">Programme</div><div class="v">16 wks</div></div></div></div><div class="case-card"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1486406146926-c627a92ad1ab?auto=format&amp;fit=crop&amp;w=900&amp;q=75" alt="CASE — Fabric" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; height: 200px; display: block; object-fit:cover;" /><span class="ctag" style="background: var(--m-orange); position: absolute;">Fabric · Façade</span><h4>Commercial — Sussex</h4><p class="cs">Rainscreen and curtain-walling upgrade to a commercial façade.</p><div class="cm"><div><div class="k">Value</div><div class="v">£1.3m</div></div><div><div class="k">Programme</div><div class="v">22 wks</div></div></div></div></div><p class="case-note">Representative of the Fabric work we are set up to deliver. Named, full-format case studies follow as projects complete — PQQ references available on request.</p></section><section class="sec tight"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 28px;"><div class="kicker">FAQs</div><h2 class="dhead sm">Envelope questions,<br>answered.</h2></div><div class="faq reveal in"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you carry out cladding remediation and building-safety works?</summary><p>Yes. We deliver cladding remediation and façade safety works on higher-risk buildings under the Building Safety Act 2022 — from intrusive survey and strip-out through to a compliant, fully documented replacement envelope.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>How do you ensure fire compliance (BS 8414 / Part B)?</summary><p>We specify and install systems with cladding fire performance assessed to BS 8414 against the BR 135 criteria, all designed to meet Building Regulations Part B. Every system is traceable, with product data and records retained for the building’s safety case.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Do you do external wall insulation and retrofit (PAS 2035)?</summary><p>Yes. We deliver external wall insulation (EWI) and fabric retrofit within the PAS 2030 / 2035 framework, improving thermal performance to Part L while keeping the fire strategy and detailing correct.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Can you work on occupied buildings and at height safely?</summary><p>Yes. Most envelope work is at height around live, occupied buildings. We plan access — scaffold, MEWPs and mast-climbers — and sequence the works elevation-by-elevation under CDM 2015 to keep residents and the public safe.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>What warranties come with the envelope?</summary><p>You get manufacturer product warranties on the cladding, render, roofing or insulation system, backed by our workmanship warranty — plus a full records pack covering the specification, installation and inspection.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>Which areas do you cover?</summary><p>We deliver fabric and building-envelope packages across London and the South East, including Sussex, Surrey, Kent, Hampshire and Berkshire. Send us the site address and we’ll arrange a survey.</p></details></div></section><section class="sec tight line-top"><div class="reveal in" style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><div class="kicker">The other three lines</div><h2 class="dhead sm">One contractor,<br>four service lines.</h2></div><div class="otherlines reveal in"><div class="otherline"><span class="ol-l"><span class="ol-sw" style="background: var(--m-green);"></span><span class="o